4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO MULTIDISTRICT
5 AGREEMENTS BETWEEN SCHOOL DISTRICTS; INCREASING THE FLEXIBILITY OF SCHOOL DISTRICTS
6 TO ENTER INTO MULTIDISTRICT AGREEMENTS; PROVIDING A COUNTYWIDE RESOURCE-SHARING
7 INCENTIVE THROUGH THE TOTAL QUALITY EDUCATOR PAYMENT FOR SCHOOL DISTRICTS THAT
8 ESTABLISH CERTAIN MULTIDISTRICT AGREEMENTS WITH ALL DISTRICTS IN A COUNTY; ALLOWING
9 MULTIDISTRICT AGREEMENTS TO INCLUDE PRIVATE ENTITIES; AMENDING SECTIONS 20-3-363 AND
10 20-9-306, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 Section 1. Section 20-3-363, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "20-3-363. Multidistrict agreements -- fund transfers. (1) (a) The boards of trustees of any two or
16 more school districts may enter into a multidistrict agreement to create a multidistrict cooperative to perform any
17 services, activities, and undertakings of the participating districts, including full and to provide for the joint
18 funding and operation and maintenance of all programs and services of the participating districts upon the
19 terms and conditions as may be mutually agreed to by the districts subject to the conditions of this section.
20 (b) A multidistrict agreement may include an agreement through which one district provides
21 culturally rooted instruction aligned to a learning environment for English language learners or an Indian
22 language immersion program to pupils of a district participating in the multidistrict agreement. The costs and
23 other terms of service must be reflected in the multidistrict agreement.
24 (c) An agreement must include provisions for dissolution of the cooperative, including the
25 conditions under which dissolution may occur and the disposition of any remaining funds that had been
26 transferred to an interlocal cooperative fund in support of the cooperative. An agreement must be approved by
27 the boards of trustees of all participating districts and must include a provision specifying terms upon which a
28 district may exit the multidistrict cooperative. The agreement may be for a period of up to 3 years.
